Armed bandits struck again In Kaduna,  killing a Professor’s son while kidnapping his father. Independent learnt that this took place around 10:15pm Sunday night. Armed kidnappers stormed Kuregu community in Wusasa, Zaria and whisked away a university professor. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Independent gathered that, “They met Prof. Aliyu outside, beat him before kidnapping him.” “Abdul (His son) came out of the house after he heard his father’s scream. Before he reached the place where his father was, they shot him dead. Kebbi Gov’t. Reconstructs 1,050 Shops At N2bn, Says Gov. Bagudu New Commissioner Of Police In Adamawa Calls For Public’s Cooperation “They proceeded to break into the house to look for more people. His other son, Khalifa, escaped before they could gain entrance,” The source added. Another family member was also shot but is currently receiving treatment. The professor, identified as Aliyu Waziri, is a staff of Abubakar Tafawa Balewa University (ATBU), Bauchi. It was disclosed that his murdered son was buried this morning according to Islamic rites. However, the Kidnappers are yet to call the family to make demands/ransom. Independent gathered.